#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:5
msgid "Modularized Output"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:7
msgid ""
"By default, emscripten outputs regular JS scripts which can be loaded on the "
"Web via a ``script`` tag, or on the command line using Node or other JS "
"runtime."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:10
msgid ""
"In this default configuration the generated :ref:`module` variable (and "
"indeed all of the emscripten internal symbols) are added to the global "
"scope.  This means that only one emscripten-built program can be loaded in a "
"given scope (since multiple modules would clobber each other's state)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:15
msgid ""
"The :ref:`modularize` setting (along with other related settings) can be "
"used to isolate the generated module within its own private scope and/or "
"allow multiple instances of the same module to be created."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:19
msgid ""
"This section covers the various modularization options available and how to "
"use them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:24
msgid "Using -sMODULARIZE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:26
msgid ""
"The :ref:`modularize` setting has two primary functions.  Firstly, it puts "
"all of the generated code inside its own scope so that the global namespace "
"is not polluted when the JS is loaded (for example, via ``script`` tag). "
"Secondly, it allows multiple instances of the module to be created."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:31
msgid ""
"The generated factory function is async and it returns a promise of an "
"instance of the program.  It can be called any number of times to create "
"multiple separate and isolated instances of the same program."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:35
msgid ""
"By default, the factory function is called ``Module``, but it can be given a "
"unique name via the ``-sEXPORT_NAME`` setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:38
msgid ""
"For example, a program built using ``-sMODULARIZE -sEXPORT_NAME=Foo`` can be "
"instantiated using:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:47
msgid "or:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:55
msgid ""
"If node is included in the ``-sENVIRONMENT`` setting then the generated "
"module also acts as a ``CommonJS`` module under node."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:58
msgid ""
"Because there is no global ``Module`` object in this case any parameters to "
"the module creation are passed via the optional parameter to the factory "
"function. For example, if you wanted to use a custom ``print`` method you "
"could write:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:68
msgid "Generating ES6 Modules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:70
msgid ""
"The :ref:`EXPORT_ES6` setting can be used to instead output JavaScript in "
"the form of an ES module.  (The ES module format did not exist at time when "
"the `MODULARIZE` setting was first created otherwise this would likely be "
"the default)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:75
msgid ""
"Using an output filename that ends in `.mjs` will automatically enable this "
"setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:78
msgid ""
"In this mode the module has a single default export which is the factory "
"function for creating new instances of the module.  For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:86
msgid ""
"The name ``Foo`` here can be whatever you choose and will always be assigned "
"to the default export of the module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:91
msgid "Using -sMODULARIZE=instance (experimental)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:93
msgid ""
"Emscripten has experimental support for performing only the encapsulation "
"part of modularization, and not the ability to create multiple instances.  "
"In this mode a module is created that exports a single instance of the "
"program rather than a factory function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:98
#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:141
msgid ""
"This setting implicitly enables :ref:`export_es6` and will not work when :"
"ref:`export_es6` is explictly disabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:101
msgid ""
"In this mode the default export of the module is an initializer function "
"which allows input parameters to be passed to the instance.  Other elements "
"normally found on the module object are instead exported directly.  For "
"example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:113
#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:155
msgid "Limitations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:115
msgid ""
"Some major features still do not work in this mode.  Many of these we hope "
"to fix in future releases.  Current limitations include:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:118
msgid ""
"Internal usage (e.g. usage within EM_JS / JS library code) of the ``Module`` "
"global does not work.  This is because symbols are exported directly using "
"ES6 module syntax rather than using the ``Module`` global."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:122
msgid "The ``wasmExports`` internal global does not exist."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:124
msgid "`ccall`/`cwrap` are not supported (depends on the ``Module`` global)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:126
msgid ":ref:`minimal_runtime` is not supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:128
msgid ""
"The output of file_packager is not compatible so :ref:`emcc-preload-file` "
"and :ref:`emcc-embed-file` do not work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:133
msgid "Source Phase Imports (experimental)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:135
msgid ""
"`Source phase imports`_ is a JavaScript proposal that adds support for "
"importing Wasm modules via ES import statements.  This allows Emscripten to "
"elide some of the auto-generated code for finding and fetching the Wasm "
"binary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:139
msgid "See :ref:`source_phase_imports`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:146
msgid "ES Module Integration (experimental)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:148
msgid ""
"`Wasm ESM integration`_ is a WebAssembly proposal that allows Wasm instances "
"to be imported directly as ES modules.  This allows Emscripten to elide a "
"lot of boilerplate code for linking up Wasm and JavaScript."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:152
msgid "See :ref:`wasm_esm_integration`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:157
msgid ""
"This setting implicitly enables :ref:`export_es6` and sets :ref:`MODULARIZE` "
"to ``instance``.  Because of this all the same limitations mentioned above "
"for ``-sMODULARIZE=instance`` apply."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:161
msgid "Some additional limitations are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:163
msgid ":ref:`wasm_workers` is not yet supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:165
msgid ""
":ref:`abort_on_wasm_exceptions` is not supported (requires wrapping wasm "
"exports)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:168
msgid ":ref:`asyncify` is not supported (depends on ``wasmExports`` global)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:170
msgid "Setting :ref:`wasm` to ``0`` is not supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Modularized-Output.rst:172
msgid "Setting :ref:`wasm_async_compilation` to ``0`` is not supported."
msgstr ""
